    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Benjamin Rush Center Acquired by Four Winds</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By PETER BELLER</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Beller, Peter</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Four Winds Hospitals, which operates psychiatric hospitals, acquires Benjamin Rush Center in Syracuse, NY, for about $4 million (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Four Winds Hospitals, which operates psychiatric hospitals in Westchester and Saratoga Springs, has acquired the Benjamin Rush Center in Syracuse for about $4 million.</p>
        <p>Four Winds became a consultant to the financially troubled,  107-bed Syracuse hospital in January 1999. It took full control of the center, now known as Four Winds-Syracuse, on May 9, operating it as a joint venture with the Psychiatric Institute of Washington.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Four Winds Hospitals, which operates psychiatric hospitals in Westchester and Saratoga Springs, has acquired the Benjamin Rush Center in Syracuse for about $4 million.</p>
        <p>Four Winds became a consultant to the financially troubled,  107-bed Syracuse hospital in January 1999. It took full control of the center, now known as Four Winds-Syracuse, on May 9, operating it as a joint venture with the Psychiatric Institute of Washington.</p>
        <p>Samuel Klagsbrun, executive medical director of Four Winds, said that most of the staff will be retained.</p>
        <p>PETER BELLER</p>
        <p>IN BUSINESS</p>
      </block>
